<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: NBC ON TOP BUT FOX HAPPY TOO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It was business as usual at the top of the TV chart that the A.C. Nielsen Co. 
released Tuesday, with NBC boasting seven of last week's 10 most watched 
programs -- starting with its Thursday night comedies. It was the 55th 
consecutive week that NBC placed first. The full list of ratings is on Page 8. 
</P>
<P>
* There was bigger news further down the chart, however, as the Fox network 
attracted what it said was its biggest audience share ever Sunday night. Both 
"America's Most Wanted" at 8 p.m. and the premiere of "Totally Hidden Video" at 
8:30 p.m. drew 20% of the available viewers to finish second in the time period 
ahead of NBC and ABC. Only CBS' "Murder, She Wrote" fared better. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
TV RATINGS 
</P>
