<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Producers John Moffitt and Pat Tourk Lee, whose recent credits include "Not 
Necessarily the News," cable-TV's ACE Awards and the "Comic Relief" fund 
raisers, will be the executive producers of the prime-time Emmy Awards telecast 
Sept. 17. It's Lee's first Emmy assignment. Moffitt was producer-director for 
the Emmys in 1978 and director in 1976. Fox Broadcasting will carry the Emmy 
telecast, the network's third in a 3-year pact with the Academy of Television 
Arts &amp; Sciences. ALEENE MacMINN 
