<TEXT>
<P>
Randall Terry, the founder of the anti-abortion group Operation Rescue, which 
staged demonstrations at the Democratic National Convention in Atlanta last 
summer, has been arrested in that city on charges stemming from the protests. 
Operation Rescue spokesman Joseph Foreman said Terry was a "political 
prisoner." Foreman said there were no plans to post the required $50,000 bond 
to release Terry, who was charged with one count of being party to a crime and 
three counts of criminal trespass stemming from the demonstrations. His 
Binghamton, N.Y.-based group has sponsored numerous protests nationwide. Terry 
was arrested after he finished an appearance before the Christian Booksellers 
Assn. to promote a book. 
