<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: RAIDS UNCOVER ALLEGED GAMBLING IN PREP SPORTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An alleged gambling operation that might have involved game-fixing at the high 
school level was uncovered in raids that confiscated more than $500,000 in 
Florence, Ala., the FBI said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Florence police chief Rick Thompson was quoted in the Florence Times Daily and 
The Birmingham News as saying coaches may have been involved in the alleged 
scheme. 
</P>
<P>
"Allegations brought forth during this investigation show that high school 
coaches and officials are manipulating the outcome of high school sporting 
events to cover the point spread given by odds makers," Thompson told the Times 
Daily. "In turn, these so-called coaches and officials have been tampering with 
the lives and future careers of our high school athletes." 
</P>
