<P>
Checchi Gets Request for Data: The Department of Transportation asked Los 
Angeles investor Alfred A. Checchi for more details about his proposed 
$4.05-billion acquisition of the parent of Northwest Airlines. DOT said it 
wanted financial forecasts, aircraft acquisition plans and details about debt 
