<P>
Merger Postponed: The U.S. 9th Circuit Court in San Francisco granted the 
California attorney general's request to postpone for 30 days the merger of 
American Stores' Lucky and Alpha Beta supermarket chains, according to Sanford 
N. Gruskin, an assistant attorney general. The delay was granted so that the 
attorney general's office could appeal to the Supreme Court in the hope of 
permanently blocking the merger, which it claims will result in higher food 
prices. Gruskin said that for the postponement to take effect the attorney 
general's office must post a bond to cover any losses that American Stores 
might incur should the Supreme Court turn down the appeal. The size of that 
bond is to be determined by the U.S. District Court in Los Angeles. 
</P>
