<TEXT>
<P>
Actress Zsa Zsa Gabor pleaded innocent today to slapping a motorcycle officer 
who stopped her Rolls Royce on La Cienega Boulevard June 14 for having expired 
tags. 
</P>
<P>
The often-married Hungarian-born actress appeared in Beverly Hills Municipal 
Court and denied one count each of battery on a police officer, disobeying a 
police officer and having an expired driver's license. Gabor, who lists her age 
as 66, also pleaded innocent to two infractions: having an open container of 
alcohol in a vehicle and having an expired vehicle registration. 
