<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
MCGRAW-HILL BUYS UNIXWORLD MAG. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
McGraw-Hill Inc. said today it has bought Mountain View, Calif.-based Tech 
Valley Publishing, including UnixWorld magazine, for an undisclosed cash sum. 
</P>
<P>
UnixWorld, a monthly magazine geared for users of Unix, a growing computer 
operating system for mainframes and personal computers, will become part of 
McGraw-Hill's computers and communications group, the company said. Joseph L. 
Dionne, McGraw-Hill chairman, said the acquisition will give the company "an 
immediate, market-leading presence in this market segment." 
</P>
<P>
McGraw-Hill also publishes BYTE magazine for the personal computing market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
