<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
GRADES TACKLE TOP TAR HEEL RUSHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHAPEL HILL, N.C. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kennard Martin, last season's leading rusher in the Atlantic Coast Conference, 
will sit out North Carolina's 1989 football season because of his problems in 
the classroom, Tar Heel Coach Mack Brown says. 
</P>
<P>
"Kennard Martin will not play football at the University of North Carolina this 
season for continued academic inconsistencies," Brown said in a statement. "He 
will remain on scholarship this fall, and his status will again be reviewed at 
the conclusion of the fall semester." 
</P>
</TEXT>
