<HEADLINE>
<P>
IT'S ACES AND EAGLE FOR TEEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
YORK, Neb. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It was a round Derek Nannen of Geneva won't forget, with two aces and an eagle 
in a six-hole span in the first round of the Nebraska State Junior 
Championships at York Country Club on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Nannen, 16, shot his first hole-in-one on the 153-yard No. 11, a par 3. On the 
next hole, a 497-yard par 5, Nannen carded an eagle 3 when he holed his third 
shot at a distance he said was about 80 yards. 
</P>
<P>
"Somehow I just knew I was going to make that shot," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Nannen recorded his second ace on the par 3, 135-yard No. 16. 
</P>
<P>
The Geneva golfer used his two aces to record an even-par 70 for the first 18 
holes of the tournament. He was seventh in Class A at the end of the two rounds 
Tuesday, posting a 70-79 -- 149. 
</P>
<P>
"It was too bad I couldn't keep it up on the second 18," Nannen said. "I didn't 
hit my irons on the second 18 nearly as well as I was on the front 18." 
</P>
</TEXT>
